parameters.name: AddressFamily
parameters.description:
The IP address family. Valid values:

*   IPv4
*   IPv6

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request. You can use the client to generate the token, but you must make sure that the token is unique among different requests. The `token` can contain only ASCII characters and cannot exceed 64 characters in length. For more information, see [How to ensure idempotence](~~25693~~).

parameters.name: Description
parameters.description: The description of the prefix list. The description must be 2 to 256 characters in length and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: Entry
parameters.description: The details of entries in the prefix list.

parameters.name: MaxEntries
parameters.description: The maximum number of entries that the prefix list can contain. Valid values: 1 to 200.

parameters.name: PrefixListName
parameters.description: The name of the prefix list. The name must be 2 to 128 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, colons (:), underscores (\_), periods (.), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter and cannot start with `http://`, `https://`, `com.aliyun`, or `com.alibabacloud`.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The ID of the region in which to create the prefix list.

parameters.name: ResourceGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the resource group to which to assign the prefix list.

parameters.name: Tag
parameters.description: The tags to add to the prefix list.
